page.title: 13WEBBINGTON COUNTRY CLUB
page.content: TRAVELLERS EYES ARE CAUGHT BY THIS LARGE BLACK AND WHITE FRONTED BUILDING,WHICH SITS ON THE SLOPES OF MENDIP OVERLOOKING THE LOX-YEO VALLEY.THIS IS THE WEBBINGTON COUNTRY CLUB. THE CLUB HAS HAD A SERIES OF OWNERS OVER THE PAST TEN YEARS.THE BUILDINGS HAVE BEEN EXTENDED AND TWICE THEY HAVE SUFFERED DAMAGE BY FIRE. HOWEVER,PEOPLE OF ALL AGES AND FROM A WIDE CATCHMENT AREA,HAVE BEEN ATTRACTED TO THE CLUB.THIS HAS BEEN THE RESUL OF GOOD FOOD AND FIRST CLASS ENTERTAINMENT BEING AVAILABLE.THE CLUB HAS FOUR BARS,THREE RESTAURANTS,A CABARET ROOM AND A HEALTH SPA. IT IS NOW SLOWLY RECOVERING FROM THE LAST FIRE.
